Heat broiler or grill to high. Bring @water{1 1/2%cups} to a boil with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} in a #small pot{}. Rinse @Tri-Colored Quinoa{1/2%cup} in a #fine mesh
strainer{}. Pick @Basil{1/2%ounce} leaves; add stems to pot. Once water boils,
add quinoa. Reduce to a simmer, cover, and cook until tender, about
~{15%minutes}. Transfer to #large bowl{}; discard stems.

Meanwhile, trim woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{6%ounce}. Halve
@Yellow Squash{2} crosswise, then cut each half into 6 wedges. Roughly chop
@Black Olives{1%ounce}. Place basil leaves in a stack, then slice into thin
ribbons.

Toss together squash, @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}, salt, pepper, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{2%tsp}
(we sent more) on a #baking sheet{}. Place under broiler and broil until just
starting to brown, about ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: If grilling, place oiled and seasoned squash over direct heat and grill until
> starting to char, about 10 minutes.

Remove baking sheet from broiler and give squash a toss, keeping it toward one
side of sheet. Add asparagus to other side of sheet and toss with a drizzle of
@Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Return sheet to broiler and
continue broiling until squash is nicely browned and asparagus is tender,
~{7-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If grilling, flip squash, then add asparagus to grates and grill until
> tender and charred, 7-10 minutes.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @Red Wine Vinegar{1%tbsp},
@Dijon Mustard{2%tsp}, @Honey{1/2%ounce}, and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season with
salt and pepper. Once veggies are done, set aside a few pieces for garnish. Cut
remaining veggies into bite-sized pieces. Add to bowl with quinoa along with
olives, half the @Feta Cheese{1/2%cup}, half the basil, and half the
@Sunflower Seeds{1%ounce}. Pour in half the dressing and toss to combine.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide quinoa mixture between plates and top with remaining veggies, basil,
sunflower seeds, and feta. Drizzle remaining dressing over plate and serve.